node.statement: OVERVIEW: We compute the commutator [g_1, g_2] = g_1^{-1} g_2^{-1} g_1 g_2 by tracing all 7 elements of {1,2,3,4,5,6,7} through the composition. Using the convention that (sigma tau)(x) = sigma(tau(x)), we compute [g_1, g_2](x) = g_1^{-1}(g_2^{-1}(g_1(g_2(x)))) for each x. We identify the orbits and express the result in disjoint cycle notation.
